<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2><HR />
<p>
  Fleetbuilding for hard content is something many players struggle with. This
  guide hopes to give a comprehensive overview of fleetbuilding for hard content
  in Azur Lane.
</p>
<p>
  <b
    >This guide assumes all ships are properly geared, check out gear guides for
    more information.</b
  >
</p>
<br />

<h2 id="just_started">If you just started Azur Lane...</h2><hr
  class="custom-hr"
/>
<p>
  Just stick to 1 fleet for now and ignore this guide. This guide is meant for
  mid-game players who have enough ships leveled to get a second fleet going.
</p>
<p>
  You can use <b
    >unlocking <WikiLink page="Operation Siren">Operation Siren</WikiLink></b
  > as a benchmark. Once you have unlocked Operation Siren, come back to this guide.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        >Note: When farming, refer to the <a
          href="farming"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Farming Guide</a
        > for more information</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

<h2 id="mob_vs_boss">Mob Fleet vs Boss Fleet</h2><HR />
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><b>Mob Fleet:</b></p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>Kills everything on the stage that is <b>NOT</b> the main boss.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Built to sustain multiple battles in a row.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Can be used for leveling ships.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Used for 90% of all Azur Lane content.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<br />
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><b>Boss Fleet:</b></p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p><b>ONLY</b> attacks the main boss of the stage.</p>
    </li>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Boss Fleet ships should be at full health going into the fight.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          There is also an <WikiLink page="Combat#Ammo">Ammo Bonus</WikiLink> damage
          advantage.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <li>
      <p>Built to do the maximum amount of damage in 1 fight.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Has your best ships and gear.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<br />

