<h2 id="damage_stagger">Fast Loads / Staggering Damage</h2><hr
  class="custom-hr"
/>
<p>
  Having all your BB shots or CV airstrikes overkill a wave does not help with
  clear times. This is why staggering damage helps.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        >Consult a tierlist or other guide for ship viability. Ships are NOT
        ordered by viability.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        >Ships in this category also fulfil other roles (sometimes multiple!),
        which are marked accordingly. The role listed is the role I would
        personally use them in.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        >Some ships are more strict with requirements to Fast Load than others,
        so be wary of ruining your fleet composition. Read skills for details!</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Ways to stagger damage:</p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Slightly adjusting Planes (CVs) or Main Guns (BBs) can help stagger
        damage slightly.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Some equipment can also help stagger volleys or airstrikes. Read
        equipment skills for details.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Using one of the ships listed below that have built-in stagger through
        their skills.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<br />

<h2 id="skill_sync">Skill Syncing</h2><HR />

<h3 id="timed_skill">Timed Skill Syncing</h3>

<h4 class="fs-5">20 Second Syncing:</h4>
<p>
  <i>Example: <WikiLink page="Helena" title="Helena">Helena</WikiLink></i>
</p>
<p>
  With standard equipment, all backline options sync with <WikiLink
    page="Helena"
    title="Helena">Helena</WikiLink
  > for at least 2-3 strikes.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        ><WikiLink page="Helena" title="Helena">Helena</WikiLink> has different sync
        timings when equipped with a <WikiLink
          page="SG Radar#Type 3-0"
          title="SG Radar">SG Radar</WikiLink
        >. When equipping an SG Radar, she cannot sync with most CVs.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

<h4 class="fs-5">15 Second Syncing:</h4>
<p>
  Don't bother with syncing to 15s. BBs need the <WikiLink
    page="Twin 457mm (Mark A Prototype)"
    title="Prototype Twin 457mm Mk A Main Gun Mount"
    >Prototype Twin 457mm Mk A Main Gun Mount</WikiLink
  >, and CVs can't sync to this at all.
</p>
<br />

<h3 id="on_shot_sync">On Shot / Strike Syncing</h3>
<p>
  <i>
    Example:
    <WikiLink page="Vanguard" title="Vanguard">Vanguard</WikiLink>,
    <WikiLink page="Duke of York" title="Duke of York">Duke of York</WikiLink>,
    <WikiLink page="Ark Royal" title="Ark Royal">Ark Royal</WikiLink>,
    <WikiLink page="Implacable" title="Implacable">Implacable</WikiLink>,
    <WikiLink page="Centaur" title="Centaur">Centaur</WikiLink>
  </i>
</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>
      Read ship skills to see what timings are necessary, and see if a ship
      needs to launch first/last.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Adjust equipment such that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          All ships launch at roughly the same time (within 1 second of each
          other).
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Ships that need to launch first/last are able to launch first/last
          without issues.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
<br />

<h3 id="faction_fleets">Faction Fleets</h3>
<p>
  Faction Fleets are sub-optimal. A well-built mixed faction fleet will perform
  better than a well-built faction fleet 100% of the time.
</p>

<h3 id="pair_skills">Pair Skills</h3>
<p>
  These are ships that receive buffs from sortieing with specific ships (usually
  ships of the same faction).
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>1-2</b> Ships Needed: It is fine to build the fleet around this buff.
    </p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Example: <WikiLink page="Howe" title="Howe">Howe's</WikiLink>
        <span class="red_skill">Covenant of the Immortal Knights</span>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>3+</b> Ships Needed, and the benefit is <b>good</b>: It is fine to
      build the fleet around this buff.
    </p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Example: <WikiLink page="Shinano" title="Shinano">Shinano's</WikiLink>
        <span class="blue_skill">Protector of the New Moon</span>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>3+</b> Ships Needed, and the benefit is <b>mediocre / bad</b>: It is
      fine to ignore this buff.
    </p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Example: <WikiLink page="Bellona" title="Bellona">Bellona's</WikiLink>
        <span class="blue_skill">Throwing Down the Gauntlet</span>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>Bad</b> Ships Needed: Don't build the fleet around this buff.
    </p>
  </li>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Example: <WikiLink page="Portland" title="Portland">Portland's</WikiLink
        >
        <span class="red_skill">Best Sister</span>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<br />

<h2 id="damage_distribution">Damage Distribution</h2><HR />
<h3 id="backline_dmg_dist">Backline</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      The <b>Flagship</b> generally takes the most damage. All ramming boat / plane
      damage distribution is random, so be careful!
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Due to concealment, CV/Ls are generally safe when they are not revealed.
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

<h3 id="vanguard_dmg_dist">Vanguard</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      The <b>Main Tank</b> takes the most damage. The <b>Off-Tank</b> takes the 2nd
      most damage. The <b>Protected</b> (Middle) Slot takes the least damage.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        >For ADVANCED PLAYERS: To determine relative ship bulk, check out this <a
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          target="_blank"
          href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1HF6_hLEB8m_v0stp4DLGnIoDjgojvo7fjYz-cysjTMc/edit#gid=0"
          title="Mebot EHP Sheet">EHP Sheet</a
        > by @mebot. Sheet and numbers are a work in progress, and may not accurately
        reflect in-game bulk / performance.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

